{"published time": "2024-02-27T22-20-00-00-00", "images": ["https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/ft.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage1.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage2.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage3.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage4.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage5.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage6.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage7.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage8.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage9.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage10.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage11.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage12.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage13.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage14.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage15.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage16.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage17.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage18.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage19.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage20.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage21.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage22.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage23.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage25.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage26.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage28.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage29.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage30.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage31.webp", "https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage32.webp"], "content": "<div class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n <img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\" height=\"683\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/ft.webp\" srcset=\"https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/ft.webp\" width=\"1024\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"entry-content\">\n <p>\n  <em>\n   Publicamos una traducci\u00f3n no oficial de un art\u00edculo publicado en\n  </em>\n  <a href=\"https://www.causedupeuple.org/2024/02/26/photographies-paris-hommage-aux-heros-du-proletariat/\">\n   La causa de la gente\n  </a>\n  <em>\n   .\n  </em>\n </p>\n <p>\n  Este domingo 25 de febrero, la causa del du Peuple pidi\u00f3 conmemorar a los h\u00e9roes del proletariado de Francia. Como cada a\u00f1o, este evento conmemorativo ten\u00eda como objetivo honrar a Pierre Overney, trabajador revolucionario, vendedor de La Cause du Peuple. El 25 de febrero de 1972, mientras Pierrot estaba teniendo la dura experiencia de desempleo forzado, despedido de Renault por razones pol\u00edticas, particip\u00f3 en una acci\u00f3n para distribuir folletos frente a la f\u00e1brica para conmemorar el d\u00e9cimo aniversario de la masacre del metro Charonne, una manifestaci\u00f3n que sigui\u00f3 a la masacre del 17 de octubre de 1961, donde la polic\u00eda francesa sofoc\u00f3 masivamente argelinos. Despu\u00e9s de su muerte, la solidaridad de la clase era inmensa, y m\u00e1s de 200,000 personas caminaron en una larga procesi\u00f3n detr\u00e1s de su ata\u00fad a principios de marzo de 1972.\n </p>\n <p>\n  Tambi\u00e9n rindimos homenaje especial a los h\u00e9roes del Grupo Manouchian (FTP-Moi), dando sus vidas para el Partido Comunista y la Revoluci\u00f3n hace 80 a\u00f1os. Adem\u00e1s de un discurso, se leyeron dos cartas a los camaradas presentes. El primero est\u00e1 compuesto por extractos de la carta de Missak Manouchian a M\u00e9lin\u00e9e, su esposa, antes de su muerte. Ella demuestra todo su internacionalismo y hero\u00edsmo. La segunda es una carta del trabajador b\u00falgaro Lutibrodsky, condenado a muerte por la dictadura en 1934, a su padre. Esta carta se distribuy\u00f3 en miles de copias en ese momento como un ejemplo de la implacable lucha contra la burgues\u00eda y el fascismo. La manifestaci\u00f3n, que comienza desde la estaci\u00f3n de metro de P\u00e8re Laachaise, pasada por la tumba de Pierrot, luego a la \u00fanica, luchador comunista, jud\u00edo polaco y miembro del grupo de Manouchian, que recibi\u00f3 un disparo el 21 de febrero de 1944.\n </p>\n <p>\n  Estamos publicando aqu\u00ed fotos del evento, que atrajeron la atenci\u00f3n y la simpat\u00eda de los transe\u00fantes y los empleados de P\u00e8re Laachaise [Nota del traductor: un cementerio en Par\u00eds], movilizando a muchos seguidores de nuestro peri\u00f3dico. Muy pronto publicaremos el discurso y las cartas que se leyeron en esta ocasi\u00f3n.\n </p>\n <figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n  <figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\">\n   <img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9300\" data-id=\"9300\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"683\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage1.webp\" srcset=\"https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage1.webp\" width=\"1024\"/>\n  </figure>\n  <figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\">\n   <img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9309\" data-id=\"9309\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"683\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage2.webp\" srcset=\"https://redherald.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/homenage2.webp\" widt